 {"id":"bd-ncmx","title":"Define ConformanceTarget trait and test infrastructure","description":"## Overview

Define the trait that runtime implementations must implement to run conformance tests, plus test macros and utilities.

## Background

For conformance tests to work across multiple runtime implementations, we need an abstraction layer. The ConformanceTarget trait defines what capabilities a runtime must expose for testing.

## ConformanceTarget Trait

```rust
/// Trait for runtime implementations to run conformance tests.
pub trait ConformanceTarget: Sized {
    /// The runtime type.
    type Runtime;

    /// Create a new runtime instance for testing.
    fn create_runtime(config: TestConfig) -> Self::Runtime;

    /// Run a future to completion on the runtime.
    fn block_on<F>(runtime: &Self::Runtime, f: F) -> F::Output
    where
        F: Future + Send + 'static,
        F::Output: Send + 'static;

    /// Spawn a task in the current region.
    fn spawn<F>(cx: &Cx, f: F) -> TaskHandle<F::Output>
    where
        F: Future + Send + 'static,
        F::Output: Send + 'static;

    /// Create a child region.
    fn region<F>(cx: &Cx, f: F) -> RegionHandle
    where
        F: FnOnce(&Cx) + Send + 'static;

    /// Request cancellation of a region.
    fn cancel(cx: &Cx, reason: CancelReason);

    /// Advance time (for Lab runtime, may no-op for production).
    fn advance_time(runtime: &Self::Runtime, duration: Duration);
}
```

## Test Configuration

```rust
pub struct TestConfig {
    pub timeout: Duration,
    pub rng_seed: Option<u64>,
    pub tracing_enabled: bool,
}

impl Default for TestConfig {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self {
            timeout: Duration::from_secs(5),
            rng_seed: Some(42),
            tracing_enabled: false,
        }
    }
}
```

## Test Macros

```rust
/// Define a conformance test that runs against all registered targets.
#[macro_export]
macro_rules! conformance_test {
    (:ident, xpr) => {
        #[test]
        fn () {
            conformance::run_test(stringify!(), );
        }
    };
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] ConformanceTarget trait defined with all necessary operations
- [ ] TestConfig for test customization
- [ ] conformance_test! macro for writing tests
- [ ] LabRuntime implements ConformanceTarget
